The Ylang Ylang essential oil is produced by the steam distillation of the Cananga odorada Hook f. flowers; a plant native of India, Java y Filipinas, nowaday extended in the intertropical area, specially in the South and Center America and in the Comores and Magadascar. The essential oil of Ylang Ylang has a bright yellow colour with a sweet floral aroma, highly sought after in frangrance industry and aromateraphy. The essential oil of Ylang Ylang is traditionally considered an antidepressant, good to relieve the anxiety and the stress and a natural aphrodisiac.

The essential oil of Juniperberry is produced from the berries of the Juniperus communis L.; an evergreen shrub up to 6m high native from all northern hemisphere, that can be found from India to North European countries as well as in southern regions of Europe.
It has small flowers and little blue berries. The oil is steam distilled from young branches and leaves, containing or not the berries. In some places the oil is steam distilled only from the berries, giving a different product more focused for flavour applications.
The needles and berries have a long traditional history for medicinally uses and in aromatherapy.

The Argan oil is extracted from the kernel of the fruit of the Argania spinosa tree; a thorny tree endemic of the arid and semi-arid regions of Morocco and Algeria. The argan tree can
grow as high as eight to ten meters and can live up to two hundred years.
One tree produces approximately 10kg of fruit per year. The soft pulp removed from the fruit is used as feed for goats and the seeds are then cold pressed for the production of the
vegetable oil.
